<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ali Mahdi Thanks Various Officials in Address </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0101170094 Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic in 
Somali 1100 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0101170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Somali </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Ali Mahdi Mohamed, president of the Somali 
Republic, sent a congratulatory New Year 1994 message today to 
all the Somali people wherever they may be, beseeching God to 
make this year the year in which the Somali people revive their 
nationhood and find peace amidst the general public of the world 
at large. [passage omitted] 
  The president sent a message of good wishes and 
congratulations to UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali, who 
he said has selflessly stood up for the interests of the Somali 
people, noting the UN Security Council's day and night effort to 
ensure that the crisis in Somalia is resolved. The president 
sent a similar message to the UN Operation in Somalia leadership 
and staff and wished them success. 
  The president further called on the Somali community to make 
use of the international assistance which is badly needed by 
many countries in the world who also face crisis. [passage 
omitted] 
  On the formation of district and regional assemblies and 
more 
so the national assembly, the president called on the Somali 
people to speed up the formation of those assemblies which the 
world and all peace-loving people see as the only solution of 
reviving the nationhood of Somalia. The president further 
highlighted the way the 12 factions are fully involved in the 
faster formation of those assemblies in order to establish the 
interim national assembly and further called on our brothers the 
Somali National Alliance [SNA] and their supporters to be 
positive and flexible towards the peace calls by their brothers 
[the 12 factions], and if their [SNA] peace call is genuine, for 
them to participate in the formation of the assemblies, which is 
vital. 
  Today we are not in a position of confrontation and blaming 
each other but we are at the crossroads of reviving the 
nationhood of the Somali people, the president said. [passage 
omitted] 
  Finally, President Ali Mahdi Mohamed called on the Somali 
people wherever they may be to pray to God to bestow success and 
prosperity on Somalia in this year 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

