<F P=100> REPUBLIC of SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attackers' Getaway Car Found </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3112055693 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0546 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> MB3112055693 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cape Town Dec 31 SAPA -- Police have found the 
getaway car of five gunmen who on Thursday night sprayed a Cape 
Town pub with automatic rifle fire, leaving four people dead and 
five others wounded. The car, a blue Opel Rekord, was found in 
Guguletu township outside the city. 
  Police have hailed the find as a major breakthrough in their 
investigations into the massacre at the Heidelberg tavern in 
Observatory. 
  SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news 
reported police roadblocks were in place throughout the Cape 
Province and as far afield as Transkei on Friday morning. 
  No-one has accepted responsibility for the attack. 

</TEXT>

