<F P=100> REPUBLIC of SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   President's Reaction Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3112063993 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0609 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> MB3112063993 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [SAPA PR wire service issued by the government spokesman] </F>
  [Text] Media Statement by the Government Spokesman 
  Reaction by the State President, Mr F W de Klerk, to 
  the Attack Last Night on an Observatory 
  Restaurant 
  The state president has learned with shock and horror of the 
attack last night on an Observatory restaurant in which four 
people were killed. 
  The identity of those responsible for the attack is not yet 
known. The state president has, however, given the assurance 
that the South African Police will use all their resources to 
track down the perpetrators and to bring them to justice. 
  The state president has emphasised that there can be no 
justification whatsoever for this barbaric deed. The 
representatives of the vast majority of South Africans have 
reached agreements that will soon lead to our first inclusive 
national elections and to the establishment of a truly 
representative government of national unity. The attack last 
night is evidently an attempt to destabilise this process. 
  The state president has called on all South Africans to 
resist any attempt to force them to deviate from this course and 
has urged them to stand united in their condemnation of violence. 
  He has conveyed his condolences to the family and friends of 
those who lost their lives in this shocking attack. 
Issued by the government spokesman Pretoria, 31 December 1993 

</TEXT>

