<F P=100> REPUBLIC of SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PAC Says Attack `Regrettable' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3112081893 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0751 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> MB3112081893 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg Dec 31 SAPA -- The Pan Africanist 
Congress [PAC] on Friday called the late night shooting at a pub 
in Observatory, Cape Town, in which four people were killed and 
several injured, regrettable. 
  But the attack had to be seen "in the context of the daily 
carnage sweeping across our country, especially in the East Rand 
and the killing fields of Natal," said Deputy President Johnson 
Mlambo in a telephone interview with SAPA. "The PAC calls upon 
all our people to pay an equal value to all human life, 
regardless of skin colour." 
  Mr Mlambo said the PAC would continue to work hard for a 
mutual cessation of hostilities with the "regime". "We hope in 
the new year to extend our slogan of peace amongst the African 
people to apply to all who live in our country." 
  He added that the PAC did not know who was behind the 
attack. 

</TEXT>

