<H3> <TI>   Warns of More Attacks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3112111093 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1103 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> MB3112111093 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cape Town 31 Dec SAPA -- In a telephone call to SAPA 
on Friday afternoon, a Mr Zwaye Mfeya said he was the commander 
of the APLA [Azanian People's Liberation Army] unit which 
attacked the bar just before midnight on Thursday, killing four 
people and wounding five. Mr Mfeya said he was phoning from 
central Cape Town. "The Afrikaner regime should expect more 
attacks. APLA confirms these operations will continue as long 
as our people don't have the vote...Ours is the vote for 
majority rule. APLA operations will continue as long as our 
people are being maimed and killed by the SA Defence Force and 
police." 
  SAPA was unable to immediately verify the authenticity of 
the 
claim. Mr Mfeya would give no more details of the attack other 
than those reported. 

