<H3> <TI>   Call 1994 Year of `Great Offensive' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3112141793 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1326 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> MB3112141793 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Umtata Dec 31 SAPA -- The Azanian People's 
Liberation Army [APLA] has declared 1994 the year of the great 
offensive on all fronts. In a New Year's message received by a 
SAPA correspondent in Umtata, APLA commander Sabelo Phama said 
on Friday the bullet and the ballot were to be used effectively 
in 1994. 
  Mr Phama said his organisation was concerned about decisions 
pertaining to security forces at the World Trade Centre. He 
said political power without military and economic power was 
empty and APLA should double its efforts both politically and on 
the military front. 
  The statement made no mention of the attack on a Cape Town 
pub around midnight on Thursday which killed four people and 
injured others. A caller purporting to represent APLA claimed 
in a telephone conversation with SAPA his organisation, the 
armed wing of the Pan Africanist Congress, was responsible for 
the attack. 

