Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Network Africa" program] </F>
  [Text] There are reports of an attack against an American 
oil installation in the northern Angola. A spokeswoman for the 
oil company, Chevron, which runs the operation at Malongo, said 
three mortar bombs landed in the base, slightly injuring one 
person and damaging two vehicles. The Portuguese News Agency 
quoted Angolan military sources as saying the attack was 
possibly carried out by forces linked to the UNITA [National 
Union for the Total Independence of Angola] rebel movement, but 
the UNITA spokesman at the United Nations, Marcos Samondo, said 
he knew nothing about the attack. 

