<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lusaka talks are at a standstill at the request 
of the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola 
[UNITA]. The same UNITA has attacked once again, this time the 
city of Malanje. Its men moved to 8 km from the city and 
launched an attack on Angolan Armed Forces positions in Carianga 
and received a prompt response. Our correspondent Francisco 
Culipingana reports: 
  [Begin Culipingana recording] Yesterday, (?UNITA forces) 
attacked the government forces position in Carianga de Baixo 
area, some 8 km from the city of Malanje. In that operation, 
the government forces killed four rebels, recovering two AKM 
weapons, a pistol, and a bag containing assorted medicine. Due 
to the intense shelling by Jonas Savimbi's movement, the North 
East Military Front Command alerts all the defense forces in the 
province, internal security, and the residents in general to 
remain vigilant [words indistinct] (?efforts) by the rebels to 
occupy and consolidate more positions [words indistinct] the 
final stage of this festive season. A communique issued by 
General Joaquim Fernandes Luma Banja, commander of the Northeast 
Military Front, says that [words indistinct] government forces 
are on alert and will do everything to frustrate all the [word 
indistinct] by the rebels. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

