<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA, Government Clashes, Activities Wrapped Up </TI></H3>
<H4>   Operations Said Planned for Bengo Province </H4>
<F P=102> MB3112084093 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
0600 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> MB3112084093 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jonas Savimbi's National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola [UNITA] today plans to mount a 
large-scale attack on the town of (Libongo) in Bengo Province. 
This was disclosed by Colonel Manuel Cartucho, spokesman for 
the Northern Operational Front. Col. Cartucho says over the 
next few days UNITA troops also plan to occupy Caxito with the 
backing of foreign forces. 
  [Begin Cartucho recording] Between 14 and 17 December our 
forces were involved in heavy clashes. Enemy troops were 
repulsed. Right now, there are large concentrations of UNITA 
troops -- estimated at four battalions -- including foreign 
elements. They are poised to attack the (Libongo) region 
between 31 December and 1 January. If they succeed in taking 
(Libongo), UNITA forces will have created the conditions for 
moving into Caxito. The morale of our forces is high. They are 
ready to repel the enemy. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

