<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Liberia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Taylor `Deputy Minister' Reportedly Killed in Clashes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB3012144093 Paris AFP in French 1216 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> AB3012144093 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Monrovia, 30 Dec (AFP) -- An official 
representative of the National Patriotic Front of Liberia [NPFL] 
-- the main armed Liberian faction --disclosed on 30 December 
that General William Gengsen, the faction's "deputy defense 
minister," was killed on 23 December as he attempted to end 
armed clashes among the faction's soldiers. 
  The source, however, did not give the reasons for the 
shooting or the number of soldiers who took part in it. The 
incident occurred in Ganta, 60 km east of Gbarnga, which in turn 
lies 160 km northeast of Monrovia -- the headquarters for NPFL 
leader Charles Taylor. 
  An informed source reported that the clashes were sparked by 
a group of men who were demanding "allowances" in anticipation 
of their future demobilization, as well as a "special bonus" for 
Christmas. The same source further disclosed that Mr. Taylor 
was planning on traveling to the scene but was dissuaded from 
doing so by his close advisers. 
  Disarmament and demobilization of all armed Liberian 
factions 
could begin in mid-January. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

