<F P=104>  Kaduna Radio Nigeria </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The federal government says it will not carry out 
any retrenchment exercise in the civil service based on the 
International Monetary Fund recommendations. The minister of 
labor and productivity, Dr. Samuel Ogbemudia, told newsmen in 
Lagos that recent newspaper reports on the issue were unfounded. 
Dr. Ogbemudia said that government's recent pronouncement on 
industrial action was not upright to the labor movement. 

