<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Congress Urges `Participation,' `Sacrifices' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0201074494 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 0600 GMT 
01 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0201074494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Nigeria Labor Congress, NLC, has called on 
workers to participate fully and be prepared to make necessary 
sacrifices this year to save the country's democratic aspiration 
and socioeconomic well-being. In his new year message, the NLC 
president, Mr. Pascal Bafyau, said that 1994 holds another 
promise for the working class and labor unions in the nation's 
drive to democracy and struggle for economic survival. He said 
despite the experiences of last year, the working class and 
Nigerians in general should show a renewed sense of optimism, 
commitment, and confidence in the ability of the nation to 
transform its [words indistinct] in the future. Mr. Bafyau said 
that the government had taken the initiative to ensure that 
workers were in the mainstream of national output. He also 
enjoined the business community, especially transporters, 
landlords, traders, and petty businessmen to be humane in fixing 
(?tags) and prices for their goods and services to make life 
more bearable for the public. 

</TEXT>

