<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senior Official on Suspension of Military Operations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0301120394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0301120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A senior Angolan military adviser says the Angolan 
Armed Forces have temporarily suspended military operations 
throughout Angola. The special adviser to the Angolan Military 
High Command, Mr. Kundi Paiama, said however that the army would 
respond to any UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence 
of Angola] attack against government held areas. The UNITA 
movement had earlier warned the government that it would not 
return to peace talks this week if the military continued large 
scale attacks against its bases. 

</TEXT>

