Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Police have detained two senior PAC [Pan-Africanist 
Congress] members in connection with the attack last week on the 
Heidelberg Tavern in Cape Town. The two leading Western Cape PAC 
men are Michael Siyolo and Theo Mabusela. They have been held 
under Section 29 of the Internal Security Act. Four people were 
killed and five others injured in the attack. 
  Meanwhile PAC spokesman Patricia de Lille says her 
organization is very disturbed by the police action: 
  [Begin De Lille recording] It has become clear to us that it 
is now the norm that whenever something happens, like the 
massacre at Heidelberg Tavern, that the first to be arrested is 
PAC members, and we know it is the weakness of the South Africa. 
Police to bring the matters to book and every time make a 
scapegoat of the PAC members, and the PAC will not tolerate 
this. [end recording] 

