<F P=101> Togo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Confirms Boycott of General Election </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0301174094 Lome Radio Lome in French 1230 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0301174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Union for Democracy and Solidarity [UDS] 
confirms its nonparticipation in upcoming elections. In a 
communique published today and signed by its delegate general, 
Mr. Antoine Folly, the UDS said that in line with the decisions 
made on 23 November 1993 not to take part in the 23 January 1994 
legislative election in the current conditions, the party has 
not put forth a candidate to stand in that election and 
therefore no candidate can claim to have been mandated by the 
UDS. The UDS states, and I quote, it had set up conditions for 
its participation in a free and fair election and regrets that 
these conditions are not met. 

</TEXT>

