<H3> <TI>   Britain To Reestablish Military Contact </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0501074394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0501074394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Britain is to reestablish military contact with 
South Africa after a break of more than 25 years with a visit of 
a royal navy war ship and support vessel this month. The 
British Ministry of Defense said in London that it hoped the 
goodwill visit by HMS Norfolk, the first of the navy's most 
up-to-date type 23 frigates, would boost Britain's chances of 
selling military equipment, particularly naval vessels, to South 
Africa. The Norfolk and its support vessel, Grey Wilbur, will 
visit Cape Town and Simonstown from 27 to 31 January. 

</TEXT>

