<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Accused of Bombing 3 Cities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0601082994 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0601082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The search for peace has resumed in the Zambian 
capital, Lusaka. However, the main strategy of Luanda is to 
continue exterminating the populations within the framework of 
the prolonged political and tribal genocide, while it falsely 
sings the song of negotiations. Our central news desk yesterday 
received reports from Uige that two SU-22 fighters coming from 
Luanda dropped a deadly cargo of bombs over the cities of Uige 
Negage and Quitexe. Many civilians were killed and others 
wounded. However, we do not have exact information and numbers 
of casualties caused by yet another barbarous action by the 
Futungo de Belas Palace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

