<H3> <TI>   Roundup of ANC Organization Activities </TI></H3>
<H4>   SDU's Said Involved in Violence </H4>
<F P=102> MB0701070994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0701070994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The defense force has said that members of 
Self-Defense Units [SDU] are involved in incidents of violence, 
making it difficult to establish peace and stability on the East 
Rand. The commander of the defense force's Group 41, Colonel 
C.P du Toit, said members of the SDU were intimidating residents 
and were in possession of illegal weapons. Earlier the ANC 
[African National Congress] appointed a commission of inquiry 
into the activities of the units. However, the Ministry of Law 
and Order believes that the Goldstone Commission should carry 
out the investigation. 

</TEXT>

