<H3> <TI>   NP Against ANC Candidates With Criminal Records </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0601195194 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1833 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0601195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria Jan 6 SAPA -- The National Party [NP] on 
Thursday condemned the African National Congress' [ANC] 
appointment of people with criminal records as election 
candidates -- referring specifically to Winnie Mandela and 
Robert McBride. "Voters must realise that in this election they 
do not vote for one candidate, but for a list of candidates," 
the NP said in a statement. 
  It mentioned that McBride, sentenced to death three times 
for 
planting a bomb which killed three and injured scores in a 
Durban pub in 1986, was pardoned along with "Wit Wolf" Barend 
Strydom who killed seven blacks when he randomly opened fire on 
them in Pretoria in 1988. 
  The NP added that the accommodation of radicals such as ANC 
Youth League President Peter Mokaba so high on ANC election 
lists was evidence of the stranglehold the South African 
Communist Party had on the ANC. 

</TEXT>

