<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   COSATU To Give New Government 5 Years To Reconstruct </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0701071294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0701071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] COSATU [Congress of South African Trade Unions] has 
given a new government five years to implement a reconstruction 
and development program. COSATU says political freedom for 
workers in 1994 will mean a vote for democracy, a vote for jobs, 
a vote for peace and a vote for improved living conditions. 
However, these objectives will be achieved only through a 
concrete program which sets out clear priorities, targets and 
time frames. 

</TEXT>

