<H3> <TI>   Update on Recent Events, Government Activities </TI></H3>
<H4>   Situation in Lome Said `Calm' </H4>
<F P=102> AB0601195094 Lome Radio Lome in French 1900 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0601195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Twenty-four hours after the commando attack on the 
Togolese Inter-Arm Regiment camp, calm broken by sporadic bursts 
of automatic gunfire now prevails in the capital, Lome. Streets 
and main highways of the city were deserted by its inhabitants 
who respected the government instructions. The curfew decreed 
yesterday evening is still in force from 1800 to 0600 and the 
land borders remain closed. The operation carried out by 
unidentified elements was preceded by an attempted attack on 
Head of State General Gnassingbe Eyadema. 

</TEXT>

