Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Eight Portuguese officers and noncommissioned 
officers are in Luanda to help train the People's Armed Forces 
for the Liberation of Angola [FAPLA] marines. The presence of 
those Portuguese soldiers in Luanda is part of military 
cooperation between the government led by Portuguese Prime 
Minister Anibal Cavaco Silva and the Popular Movement for the 
