<H3> <TI>   Government Updates Events; Border Incidents Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Mortar Shells Fired in Northern Lome </H4>
<F P=102> AB0701194094 Paris AFP in French 1841 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0701194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lome, 7 Jan (AFP) -- Mortar shells were fired early 
this evening in northern Lome, Togolese military sources told 
AFP. 
  According to these sources, a shell "fired from Ghanaian 
territory" fell at 1800, local time and GMT, on Maman Ndanida 
ward located in the northwestern suburb of the Togolese capital, 
destroying a house and seriously wounding his owner. 
  Witnesses, telephoned by AFP, also described bursts of 
automatic gunfire being heard at 1830. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

