<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   IFP Central Committee `Definitely' Not in Election </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0701190694 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 
1800 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0701190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Afrikaans </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have just received the news that the Inkatha 
Freedom Party's [IFP] Central Committee has decided the party 
will definitely not take part in the 27 April election. It will 
also not participate in any structure of the transitional 
government. 
  The Central Committee reiterated during its meeting at 
Ulundi 
that it will not participate in the Transitional Executive 
Council [TEC], nor will it recognize any decisions by the TEC. 
According to the IFP, it will only reconsider its stance when 
its constitutional proposals, as contained in the Freedom 
Alliance's document of 19 December, is accepted by the 
negotiating council. 

</TEXT>

