<F P=102>  MB0801114894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1006 GMT 08 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0801114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulundi Jan 8 SAPA -- The Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] 
announced on Saturday it will hold a special general conference 
at the end of this month. The central committee decided on 
Friday to hold the conference on January 29 and 30, according to 
a statement from the office of party leader Chief Mangosuthu 
Buthelezi. 
  The IFP Central Committee said on Friday the organisation 
will not participate in forthcoming elections unless certain 
conditions are met. The decision has been criticised by the 
National Party and the African National Congress. 

</TEXT>

